WEBVTT

1
00:01:22.916 --> 00:01:25.290
<i>As we await
more details out of Paris.</i>

2
00:01:25.291 --> 00:01:28.082
<i>we take a look back
on another life cut short.</i>

3
00:01:28.083 --> 00:01:30.124
<i>Professor Charles Xavier.</i>

4
00:01:30.125 --> 00:01:32.540
<i>The mutant leader's
assassination last year</i>

5
00:01:32.541 --> 00:01:35.374
<i>by former NSA agent Henry Gyrich</i>

6
00:01:35.375 --> 00:01:37.457
<i>has spurred increased sympathy
toward mutants</i>

7
00:01:37.458 --> 00:01:39.541
<i>despite their strange powers.</i>

8
00:01:41.791 --> 00:01:43.957
<i>But is mankind ready to share a future</i>

9
00:01:43.958 --> 00:01:47.624
<i>with those who science claims
were born to replace us?</i>

10
00:01:47.625 --> 00:01:50.416
<i>Experts debate this
and more after the break.</i>

11
00:01:52.208 --> 00:01:56.708
The buyer's really gonna throw
down 10 grand for every mutant we nab?

12
00:01:57.375 --> 00:01:59.208
Says he's using them
for target practice.

13
00:02:03.416 --> 00:02:04.416
Please don't hurt me.

14
00:02:04.417 --> 00:02:07.957
I'm Roberto da Costa.
heir to the Da Costa fortune.

15
00:02:07.958 --> 00:02:09.915
Name a price. Money's not an issue.

16
00:02:09.916 --> 00:02:11.832
Mutie thinks it's about cash.

17
00:02:11.833 --> 00:02:12.916
Funny.

18
00:02:13.458 --> 00:02:15.082
What's this freak's trick?

19
00:02:15.083 --> 00:02:16.165
No clue.

20
00:02:16.166 --> 00:02:18.290
Kid didn't even try to use his powers.

21
00:02:18.291 --> 00:02:19.916
Collared him just in case.

22
00:02:20.500 --> 00:02:21.665
Hear that. mutie?

23
00:02:21.666 --> 00:02:25.332
So long as that collar stays on.
your powers are bye-bye.

24
00:02:25.333 --> 00:02:28.165
I'm not like the ones on TV.
I'm one of the good ones.

25
00:02:28.166 --> 00:02:29.374
A good mutant?

26
00:02:29.375 --> 00:02:30.750
Now. that is rich.

27
00:02:32.291 --> 00:02:34.082
Listen. I am begging you.

28
00:02:34.083 --> 00:02:35.665
I didn't ask for this. okay?

29
00:02:35.666 --> 00:02:36.791
I was born this way.

30
00:02:37.250 --> 00:02:38.750
Ain't that the rub?

31
00:02:50.458 --> 00:02:52.625
Grab a Sentinel blaster
and spread out!

32
00:02:54.333 --> 00:02:58.083
I am Storm.
mistress of the elements.

33
00:02:58.708 --> 00:03:02.875
Surrender the boy or face my fury!

34
00:03:04.166 --> 00:03:06.208
I ain't afraid of you. you witch.

35
00:03:08.208 --> 00:03:09.666
Then you are a fool.

36
00:03:17.458 --> 00:03:20.415
Whole announcement shtick
didn't go over so well. did it?

37
00:03:20.416 --> 00:03:24.000
Pardon me. Bishop. for striving
to resolve matters peacefully.

38
00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:26.708
Real peaceful. Storm.

39
00:03:29.458 --> 00:03:30.916
Keep shooting. punks.

40
00:03:32.958 --> 00:03:36.458
Is it me. or did these dirtbags
get upgrades?

41
00:03:41.416 --> 00:03:43.915
Boot it up. boys.
X-Men are like roaches.

42
00:03:43.916 --> 00:03:46.083
You see one. more are coming.

43
00:03:55.041 --> 00:03:56.374
Good guy or bad guy?

44
00:03:56.375 --> 00:03:59.625
Name's Cyclops. Definitely the good guy.

45
00:04:03.041 --> 00:04:04.041
Hang tight.

46
00:04:28.666 --> 00:04:30.291
Kid. get down.

47
00:04:38.083 --> 00:04:41.624
How'd scum like you get your hands
on Sentinel technology?

48
00:04:41.625 --> 00:04:44.957
What? You freak shows think
we wouldn't find a way to evolve. too?

49
00:04:44.958 --> 00:04:46.999
Take his visor before he starts up again.

50
00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:49.041
No. don't! I surrender!

51
00:04:50.583 --> 00:04:52.666
Not.

52
00:04:59.500 --> 00:05:01.332
Storm and Bishop
could have been hurt.

53
00:05:01.333 --> 00:05:02.874
We needed you out there.

54
00:05:02.875 --> 00:05:05.583
You stopped the bad guys.
saved the kid.

55
00:05:07.125 --> 00:05:10.040
These beignets needed me
more than you did. <i>mon ami.</i>

56
00:05:10.041 --> 00:05:13.207
The Friends of Humanity
had retrofitted Sentinel weaponry.

57
00:05:13.208 --> 00:05:15.165
Do you have any idea
what that means. Gambit?

58
00:05:15.166 --> 00:05:19.499
Means you get to howling like
a lonely kettle left on a fiery stove.

59
00:05:19.500 --> 00:05:22.624
We've rodeo'd more Sentinels
than I care to count.

60
00:05:22.625 --> 00:05:25.624
And Storm and Bishop are made
of sterner stuff than you think.

61
00:05:25.625 --> 00:05:28.332
Rogue always come to Gambit's rescue.

62
00:05:28.333 --> 00:05:30.415
Rogue. the Professor entrusted us

63
00:05:30.416 --> 00:05:32.957
with his dream
of mutant-human coexistence.

64
00:05:32.958 --> 00:05:34.707
We have to stay vigilant.

65
00:05:34.708 --> 00:05:36.915
no matter how good things seem out there.

66
00:05:36.916 --> 00:05:38.582
The last few months have been rough.

67
00:05:38.583 --> 00:05:40.790
what with the Professor
being gone and all.

68
00:05:40.791 --> 00:05:44.332
but. sugar. if you don't simmer down.
you're gonna die of a stroke.

69
00:05:44.333 --> 00:05:45.958
Rogue is right. Cyclops.

70
00:05:47.708 --> 00:05:51.540
Scott. while I trust that
all my students would gladly die

71
00:05:51.541 --> 00:05:53.707
for my dream of a better future.

72
00:05:53.708 --> 00:05:58.624
where both human and mutant
live free of your total disdain for fun.

73
00:05:58.625 --> 00:06:00.708
I would prefer it be avoided.

74
00:06:01.708 --> 00:06:03.375
Stop being a creep. Morph.

75
00:06:07.458 --> 00:06:09.915
Look like Cyclops
about to have that stroke.

76
00:06:09.916 --> 00:06:11.583
Maybe this help.

77
00:06:22.458 --> 00:06:25.457
Remy. you could have hurt someone.

78
00:06:25.458 --> 00:06:26.750
He doesn't care. Jean.

79
00:06:27.208 --> 00:06:29.749
All he cares about
are his stupid beignets.

80
00:06:29.750 --> 00:06:32.249
I don't know who's worse.
him or Wolverine.

81
00:06:32.250 --> 00:06:34.540
Well. can everyone just please behave?

82
00:06:34.541 --> 00:06:35.832
This is a school. after all.

83
00:06:35.833 --> 00:06:38.290
and we need to be role models
for our guest.

84
00:06:38.291 --> 00:06:39.374
Jean's right.

85
00:06:39.375 --> 00:06:40.957
That kid's our only lead

86
00:06:40.958 --> 00:06:44.166
to where those extremists
got their hands on Sentinel tech.

87
00:07:04.291 --> 00:07:05.708
Salutations and welcome.

88
00:07:06.416 --> 00:07:08.915
- I'm...
- Blue. very blue. Wow.

89
00:07:08.916 --> 00:07:10.957
An astute observation. my boy.

90
00:07:10.958 --> 00:07:12.124
Hank McCoy here.

91
00:07:12.125 --> 00:07:15.124
Or if you prefer my friendly
<i>nom de guerre.</i> Beast.

92
00:07:15.125 --> 00:07:17.790
- That there at the foot of your bed is...
- Name's Jubilee.

93
00:07:17.791 --> 00:07:19.374
And. dude. I get it.

94
00:07:19.375 --> 00:07:20.540
One day. life's fresh.

95
00:07:20.541 --> 00:07:22.124
Then the next day. you're waking up

96
00:07:22.125 --> 00:07:25.457
to a blue monkey singing Mozart
as he tinkers with doohickies.

97
00:07:25.458 --> 00:07:27.665
Simian analogies. Jubilee?

98
00:07:27.666 --> 00:07:29.041
Shame on you.

99
00:07:29.166 --> 00:07:31.624
And this doohickey
is an elegant piece of art

100
00:07:31.625 --> 00:07:34.083
capable of teleporting someone
through time and space.

101
00:07:34.625 --> 00:07:36.583
Bishop's bling. He's a time traveler.

102
00:07:38.875 --> 00:07:40.457
Hank. how fares the boy?

103
00:07:40.458 --> 00:07:44.582
Besides a cavity and layman's
existential fear of metaphysics.

104
00:07:44.583 --> 00:07:46.790
Mr. Da Costa here is in perfect health.

105
00:07:46.791 --> 00:07:48.790
I need to go. Where's my jacket?

106
00:07:48.791 --> 00:07:51.415
Tell me I didn't lose it. Super expensive.

107
00:07:51.416 --> 00:07:53.415
Roberto. we can't let you go just yet.

108
00:07:53.416 --> 00:07:56.874
- Right. How much?
- "How much?"

109
00:07:56.875 --> 00:07:59.582
For the save? I was going to pay
those troops to free me. so...

110
00:07:59.583 --> 00:08:00.915
You take checks?

111
00:08:00.916 --> 00:08:04.374
We're more interested in the weapons
those creeps had.

112
00:08:04.375 --> 00:08:07.457
That giant arm was from a machine
called a Sentinel.

113
00:08:07.458 --> 00:08:10.707
Did your attackers say anything
about where they acquired it?

114
00:08:10.708 --> 00:08:12.415
Wait. wait. wait. wait. Hold up.

115
00:08:12.416 --> 00:08:15.332
Today's been a day and you're coming at me
with giant robot arms?

116
00:08:15.333 --> 00:08:18.790
Your attackers could still
be out there. child.

117
00:08:18.791 --> 00:08:20.457
Should we let you leave.

118
00:08:20.458 --> 00:08:23.165
they could find you and kill you.

119
00:08:23.166 --> 00:08:25.165
So now you're kidnapping me?

120
00:08:25.166 --> 00:08:26.332
Kidnapping?

121
00:08:26.333 --> 00:08:30.166
We wanna help mutants.
even arrogant yuppies like you.

122
00:08:31.541 --> 00:08:34.415
Look. you're scared. Roberto. I get it.

123
00:08:34.416 --> 00:08:36.332
Just give us the day to figure this out.

124
00:08:36.333 --> 00:08:37.624
make sure you're safe.

125
00:08:37.625 --> 00:08:41.374
and then you can go do
whatever a kid like you does.

126
00:08:41.375 --> 00:08:43.540
At least say there's something
to do around here

127
00:08:43.541 --> 00:08:44.916
besides listen to Mozart?

128
00:08:49.208 --> 00:08:53.790
Hear me. Humanity's days are over.

129
00:08:53.791 --> 00:08:57.124
We are nature's favored children.

130
00:08:57.125 --> 00:08:59.249
Our new age begins

131
00:08:59.250 --> 00:09:03.291
as we build a bright mutant future.

132
00:09:03.750 --> 00:09:05.332
Video games are for nerds.

133
00:09:05.333 --> 00:09:07.207
<i>It's no game. buddy.</i>

134
00:09:07.208 --> 00:09:09.540
<i>It's the Danger Room. It's where we train.</i>

135
00:09:09.541 --> 00:09:12.540
That's Magneto. the Professor's ex-bestie.

136
00:09:12.541 --> 00:09:16.415
They had. different takes
on mutant-human coexistence.

137
00:09:16.416 --> 00:09:17.707
So what can you do?

138
00:09:17.708 --> 00:09:18.832
Fly. teleport?

139
00:09:18.833 --> 00:09:21.249
<i>Shoot gold balls from your body?
That'd be weird.</i>

140
00:09:21.250 --> 00:09:22.915
But. like. he's not even real.

141
00:09:22.916 --> 00:09:25.416
You would turn your back on your own?

142
00:09:33.208 --> 00:09:35.874
<i>Better show me those powers.
tough guy.</i>

143
00:09:35.875 --> 00:09:37.625
Seriously. girl. get a life.

144
00:09:40.166 --> 00:09:41.915
Show the lady some respect.

145
00:09:41.916 --> 00:09:45.540
So scary. Jubilee. Can we stop now?

146
00:09:45.541 --> 00:09:48.625
Computer. end program.

147
00:09:50.083 --> 00:09:52.833
Scary enough for you. bub?

148
00:09:53.583 --> 00:09:57.290
<i>Agencies in the US. England
and Madripoor have been catching rumors</i>

149
00:09:57.291 --> 00:09:59.332
<i>of anti-mutant militias
with Sentinel weaponry.</i>

150
00:09:59.333 --> 00:10:02.290
<i>But this is the first I've heard
of any confirmed reports.</i>

151
00:10:02.291 --> 00:10:04.207
How are these groups
getting this tech?

152
00:10:04.208 --> 00:10:06.499
You said the UN destroyed
all the Sentinels.

153
00:10:06.500 --> 00:10:07.582
<i>And we did.</i>

154
00:10:07.583 --> 00:10:11.457
I guess I just imagined the big
robot hand that almost took out my team.

155
00:10:11.458 --> 00:10:13.207
Someone's putting this stuff out there.

156
00:10:13.208 --> 00:10:15.707
Dr. Cooper. what about Bolivar Trask?

157
00:10:15.708 --> 00:10:17.957
<i>Trask's been missing
ever since his inventions tried</i>

158
00:10:17.958 --> 00:10:21.291
<i>to swap out President Kelly's brain
with a Sentinel computer.</i>

159
00:10:21.583 --> 00:10:23.999
<i>He'd need a Master Mold factory
to build new Sentinels</i>

160
00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:26.874
<i>and you X-Men destroyed
the only one years ago.</i>

161
00:10:26.875 --> 00:10:28.457
Well. when cardio wraps.

162
00:10:28.458 --> 00:10:30.040
maybe you can spare the calories

163
00:10:30.041 --> 00:10:32.000
to go make sure
he didn't build another one.

164
00:10:32.708 --> 00:10:34.915
<i>Charles Xavier was a dear friend of mine.</i>

165
00:10:34.916 --> 00:10:38.374
<i>It's why I urged the UN Council
to work with the X-Men.</i>

166
00:10:38.375 --> 00:10:40.332
<i>A little trust. Scott.</i>

167
00:10:40.333 --> 00:10:44.457
The Professor loved to say.
"Trust happens when actions meet words."

168
00:10:44.458 --> 00:10:45.583
Cyclops out.

169
00:10:55.916 --> 00:10:57.833
Well.
this certainly explains your mood.

170
00:10:58.666 --> 00:11:00.625
Yeah. it came yesterday.

171
00:11:01.416 --> 00:11:04.415
You know. if he were here.
the team wouldn't be shooting hoops

172
00:11:04.416 --> 00:11:06.457
while slime like the Friends of Humanity

173
00:11:06.458 --> 00:11:08.540
are running around with Sentinel blasters.

174
00:11:08.541 --> 00:11:11.457
You're too hard on yourself.
and the team.

175
00:11:11.458 --> 00:11:14.415
Remember when we were young
and we'd sneak down to the lake

176
00:11:14.416 --> 00:11:16.625
instead of doing our Danger Room drills?

177
00:11:17.250 --> 00:11:20.749
Yeah.
The Professor would shout.

178
00:11:20.750 --> 00:11:24.749
"Your childish hijinks
have cost you five demerits. young man."

179
00:11:24.750 --> 00:11:26.832
And you'd say. "But. sir.

180
00:11:26.833 --> 00:11:30.375
"what's the point of being an X-Man
if we're not allowed to enjoy our lives?"

181
00:11:30.750 --> 00:11:32.582
Whoa. whoa. I did not sound like that.

182
00:11:32.583 --> 00:11:34.165
Yes. you did.

183
00:11:34.166 --> 00:11:36.416
You still sound like that.

184
00:11:37.041 --> 00:11:40.207
Those days have been on my mind
a lot lately. darling.

185
00:11:40.208 --> 00:11:43.916
You and I alone.
Our whole future ahead of us.

186
00:11:44.791 --> 00:11:47.165
The team. they'll always be family.

187
00:11:47.166 --> 00:11:49.750
but with the baby coming.

188
00:11:50.250 --> 00:11:53.790
maybe it's time to think of a life
beyond the X-Men?

189
00:11:53.791 --> 00:11:57.540
"Beyond"? You mean leave the team? Jean.

190
00:11:57.541 --> 00:11:58.999
It's like you said. Scott.

191
00:11:59.000 --> 00:12:01.040
What have we been fighting for
all these years

192
00:12:01.041 --> 00:12:03.665
if not the chance
to finally live our lives?

193
00:12:03.666 --> 00:12:06.082
We were the Professor's first students.

194
00:12:06.083 --> 00:12:07.874
The X-Men need us here.

195
00:12:07.875 --> 00:12:09.708
The team will be fine.

196
00:12:10.916 --> 00:12:12.916
Our son will need us more.

197
00:12:13.458 --> 00:12:16.416
Deep down. you know that.

198
00:12:16.916 --> 00:12:20.333
And I know it hurts.
But this one time. Scott...

199
00:12:21.708 --> 00:12:23.833
It's okay for you to let go.

200
00:12:24.291 --> 00:12:25.666
Jerk!

201
00:12:35.250 --> 00:12:38.165
Jubilee! What are you doing?

202
00:12:38.166 --> 00:12:40.207
Bozo here scared Roberto off.

203
00:12:40.208 --> 00:12:44.040
Cyclops. what if those creeps
with the Sentinel gizmos find him?

204
00:12:44.041 --> 00:12:48.957
Logan. take that nose of yours
and go find the kid.

205
00:12:48.958 --> 00:12:50.457
And take Jubilee.

206
00:12:50.458 --> 00:12:53.540
Actually. all of you could stand
to act a little more like X-Men.

207
00:12:53.541 --> 00:12:54.624
Go with them.

208
00:12:54.625 --> 00:12:57.040
Hey. now. we didn't do a dang thing.

209
00:12:57.041 --> 00:12:58.999
Took the words right out of my mouth.

210
00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:02.082
Jean may dig
the Boy Scout routine. Summers.

211
00:13:02.083 --> 00:13:05.707
but I don't much go in
for being bossed around.

212
00:13:05.708 --> 00:13:08.291
Cry me a river. Wolverine.

213
00:13:09.625 --> 00:13:10.750
Logan...

214
00:13:12.250 --> 00:13:13.666
Find Roberto.

215
00:13:14.541 --> 00:13:15.583
please.

216
00:13:18.666 --> 00:13:20.790
What Gyrich did was pretty horrible.

217
00:13:20.791 --> 00:13:24.041
But want to know the worst part
about the Professor being gone?

218
00:13:24.708 --> 00:13:25.875
You.

219
00:13:29.916 --> 00:13:32.500
- He didn't mean it.
- Doesn't matter.

220
00:13:33.041 --> 00:13:35.875
I know who we need to see
to find Bolivar Trask.

221
00:13:36.375 --> 00:13:38.916
The man who killed Charles Xavier.

222
00:13:49.166 --> 00:13:52.165
The kid's here.
but there are too many damn scents.

223
00:13:52.166 --> 00:13:53.665
Looks like we split up.

224
00:13:53.666 --> 00:13:56.541
Nice place to pass a good time. <i>chère?</i>

225
00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:18.165
If I was down there
and one of 'em brushed against my skin.

226
00:14:18.166 --> 00:14:22.207
my power-sappin' touch would leave 'em
with a nasty hangover.

227
00:14:22.208 --> 00:14:26.583
Any worthwhile man would
gladly suffer your hand in a dance.

228
00:14:33.375 --> 00:14:35.916
Thought you were gonna
slice Summers' head off back there.

229
00:14:36.458 --> 00:14:37.582
Wanna talk about it?

230
00:14:37.583 --> 00:14:41.250
Let's just find this trust-fund baby
and get out of here. Morph.

231
00:14:43.041 --> 00:14:45.249
I know what's wrong. How?

232
00:14:45.250 --> 00:14:49.165
Why. I'm Jean Grey.
humble telepath extraordinaire.

233
00:14:49.166 --> 00:14:51.999
and I'm having the most
beautiful baby in the world

234
00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:54.374
with the most boring man in the world.

235
00:14:54.375 --> 00:14:57.290
and. "Hello. you on the sidelines.

236
00:14:57.291 --> 00:15:00.457
"watching our exhausting perfection
every day."

237
00:15:00.458 --> 00:15:05.290
Perfection? If we ain't fighting Magneto.
we're dodging aliens and Sentinels.

238
00:15:05.291 --> 00:15:07.374
School's no place for a baby.

239
00:15:07.375 --> 00:15:09.749
You... Jean knows as much.

240
00:15:09.750 --> 00:15:12.499
- You don't think...
- They're leaving the team. Morph.

241
00:15:12.500 --> 00:15:13.791
Jean's leaving.

242
00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:31.290
No. no. I'm not going back there.

243
00:15:31.291 --> 00:15:33.915
Dork. let's go. You're not safe here.

244
00:15:33.916 --> 00:15:36.708
One dance. then I'll come. Promise.

245
00:15:53.916 --> 00:15:55.415
Beats that stuffy mansion. right?

246
00:15:55.416 --> 00:15:58.249
Hey. at least they're not
wasting time partying

247
00:15:58.250 --> 00:15:59.832
when they could be helping people.

248
00:15:59.833 --> 00:16:03.540
And waste the best years of my life
on some bald guy's corny dream?

249
00:16:03.541 --> 00:16:06.707
Of course. someone like you
would find a little selflessness corny.

250
00:16:06.708 --> 00:16:08.374
Peace. love. I get it.

251
00:16:08.375 --> 00:16:10.790
Does he have to make
such a big stink about it?

252
00:16:10.791 --> 00:16:14.124
Is that why you didn't use your powers
against those goons?

253
00:16:14.125 --> 00:16:16.165
Didn't want to rub their faces in it?

254
00:16:16.166 --> 00:16:17.916
It's like <i>minha mãe</i> says. Jubilee.

255
00:16:19.166 --> 00:16:20.457
Live and let live.

256
00:16:20.458 --> 00:16:22.290
Sometimes people don't get along.

257
00:16:22.291 --> 00:16:23.749
Don't I know it. bub?

258
00:16:23.750 --> 00:16:26.249
FOH ran when they saw us coming.

259
00:16:26.250 --> 00:16:28.499
Dropped one of their little toys. too.

260
00:16:28.500 --> 00:16:32.040
Pray Cyclops find where these bad boys
are coming from.

261
00:16:32.041 --> 00:16:33.750
before things get too hot to handle.

262
00:16:37.000 --> 00:16:40.749
I can't believe this fool
nearly cost us the whole future.

263
00:16:40.750 --> 00:16:42.666
He still cost us enough.

264
00:16:44.541 --> 00:16:46.874
Why would I know where Trask is?

265
00:16:46.875 --> 00:16:49.832
You helped fund his Sentinel program

266
00:16:49.833 --> 00:16:52.124
when you worked
for the Defense Department.

267
00:16:52.125 --> 00:16:54.957
Gyrich. you're serving 25 years.

268
00:16:54.958 --> 00:16:57.332
You talk and I get it down to 10.

269
00:16:57.333 --> 00:17:01.541
You mutants are moving up.
making friends in high places.

270
00:17:02.041 --> 00:17:05.040
Though it's got to hurt.
offering that deal to me.

271
00:17:05.041 --> 00:17:07.707
Those Sentinel upgrades really threw you.

272
00:17:07.708 --> 00:17:11.999
We merely hoped some humans
had evolved beyond the past.

273
00:17:12.000 --> 00:17:14.832
Did you honestly think
we'd roll over

274
00:17:14.833 --> 00:17:17.290
and let mutants take over the planet?

275
00:17:17.291 --> 00:17:18.874
That we wouldn't fight back?

276
00:17:18.875 --> 00:17:24.250
Yet your cruelty has only made
humanity more sympathetic to our cause.

277
00:17:24.666 --> 00:17:26.040
Did it?

278
00:17:26.041 --> 00:17:29.499
No. you're in vogue. Storm. A fad.

279
00:17:29.500 --> 00:17:31.500
"Look at my mutant friend."

280
00:17:32.041 --> 00:17:34.790
But under all that fashionable sympathy.

281
00:17:34.791 --> 00:17:38.999
normal people know
the more room we make for your kind.

282
00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:41.165
the less we leave for ours.

283
00:17:41.166 --> 00:17:44.040
So we might wear tolerance on our sleeves.

284
00:17:44.041 --> 00:17:46.124
but we know the naked truth.

285
00:17:46.125 --> 00:17:49.125
Tolerance is extinction.

286
00:17:50.375 --> 00:17:52.958
Ten years. Gyrich. Yours to win or lose.

287
00:17:53.625 --> 00:17:57.749
I won the day I shot the man
you freak shows look up to.

288
00:17:57.750 --> 00:18:00.582
And you get an "A" for effort.
Mr. Summers.

289
00:18:00.583 --> 00:18:03.665
but we both know you're no Charles Xavier.

290
00:18:03.666 --> 00:18:06.499
You're right. I'm not Charles Xavier.

291
00:18:06.500 --> 00:18:08.790
He'd reason with you. Be patient.

292
00:18:08.791 --> 00:18:11.832
He'd do everything in his power
to save you.

293
00:18:11.833 --> 00:18:14.916
Save me? From what. you?

294
00:18:16.083 --> 00:18:18.458
No. But have you met my wife?

295
00:18:19.583 --> 00:18:22.540
Hatred weakens your mind. Mr. Gyrich.

296
00:18:22.541 --> 00:18:25.915
Cerebro amplifies my psychic powers.

297
00:18:25.916 --> 00:18:30.040
allowing me to penetrate
your thoughts from any distance I please.

298
00:18:30.041 --> 00:18:31.790
Get out of my head!

299
00:18:31.791 --> 00:18:34.749
<i>One Master Mold is not enough.
We need backups.</i>

300
00:18:34.750 --> 00:18:36.125
<i>I know a place.</i>

301
00:18:38.333 --> 00:18:40.625
Something's wrong. Someone else...

302
00:18:50.166 --> 00:18:51.250
Whoa!

303
00:19:08.041 --> 00:19:12.041
<i>No! Not again. I'm so sorry.</i>

304
00:19:24.250 --> 00:19:29.540
<i>Behold. mutant. and despair.
for I am Death.</i>

305
00:19:29.541 --> 00:19:32.666
<i>I am Master Mold.</i>

306
00:19:39.041 --> 00:19:41.082
<i>Jean! Jean. come in!</i>

307
00:19:41.083 --> 00:19:43.124
I'm here. I'm here. Scott.

308
00:19:43.125 --> 00:19:45.040
I'm fine.

309
00:19:45.041 --> 00:19:46.665
What I felt...

310
00:19:46.666 --> 00:19:49.250
We have to stop Trask. Now.

311
00:19:50.250 --> 00:19:51.250
Listen up. people.

312
00:19:51.251 --> 00:19:54.374
Jean's psychic scan placed Trask
in the Sahara Desert.

313
00:19:54.375 --> 00:19:56.707
We fly into the coordinates. detain Trask

314
00:19:56.708 --> 00:19:58.874
and shut down Master Mold for good.

315
00:19:58.875 --> 00:20:00.832
I say we skip detaining

316
00:20:00.833 --> 00:20:04.457
and mail Trask back to the UN
in little pieces.

317
00:20:04.458 --> 00:20:07.999
There will be
no dismembering. Wolverine.

318
00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:09.165
Dismembering?

319
00:20:09.166 --> 00:20:11.957
Nah. Weight loss.

320
00:20:11.958 --> 00:20:14.208
We get this done
by working together as a team.

321
00:20:14.916 --> 00:20:16.582
Think you can do that. Logan?

322
00:20:16.583 --> 00:20:19.249
Jeez. Dad. Keep buzzing in my ear.

323
00:20:19.250 --> 00:20:21.583
What would we do if we ever lost you?

324
00:20:24.916 --> 00:20:26.375
Hang on. people.

325
00:20:30.791 --> 00:20:32.250
Cyclops!

326
00:21:00.500 --> 00:21:02.500
Another "catch the X-Men" day.

327
00:21:04.666 --> 00:21:07.541
Solid work. team. See you on the ground.

328
00:21:31.958 --> 00:21:34.083
To me. my X-Men.

329
00:21:46.958 --> 00:21:48.915
Gyrich warned me
you were coming.

330
00:21:48.916 --> 00:21:50.707
Even in prison. he has friends

331
00:21:50.708 --> 00:21:53.915
who know the mutant agenda
must be stopped.

332
00:21:53.916 --> 00:21:55.708
Trask. we don't want to fight.

333
00:21:59.166 --> 00:22:01.665
You mutants may be
the next step in evolution.

334
00:22:01.666 --> 00:22:03.790
but you're still animals

335
00:22:03.791 --> 00:22:06.333
and you need to be put down.

336
00:22:06.666 --> 00:22:08.375
Final warning. Trask.

337
00:22:14.833 --> 00:22:16.208
<i>Surrender. mutant.</i>

338
00:22:18.291 --> 00:22:22.875
<i>Surrender. mutant.
Surrender. mutant. Surrender. mutant.</i>

339
00:22:35.541 --> 00:22:36.541
Head's up.

340
00:22:49.416 --> 00:22:51.000
Greetings. enemy mine.

341
00:22:51.541 --> 00:22:54.000
Might I induce you to a change of heart?

342
00:22:55.208 --> 00:22:58.541
Louis. I think this is the beginning
of a beautiful. involuntary friendship.

343
00:23:20.916 --> 00:23:22.124
<i>Surrender. mutant.</i>

344
00:23:22.125 --> 00:23:23.583
<i>Surrender. mutant.</i>

345
00:23:24.750 --> 00:23:26.375
Give 'em the forecast.

346
00:23:27.625 --> 00:23:30.208
<i>Omega-level threat detected.</i>

347
00:23:43.250 --> 00:23:46.957
Ancient sands. heed my command

348
00:23:46.958 --> 00:23:50.041
and reclaim these relics of hatred.

349
00:24:14.833 --> 00:24:18.416
<i>You underestimate us. mutant.</i>

350
00:24:28.583 --> 00:24:30.333
Morph. belly up.

351
00:24:52.375 --> 00:24:55.874
You X-Men might use your gifts
to protect everyone.

352
00:24:55.875 --> 00:24:59.040
but all you do is remind us
that our days are numbered.

353
00:24:59.041 --> 00:25:02.082
that humanity itself is obsolete.

354
00:25:02.083 --> 00:25:05.958
You've no idea how it feels
to be left behind by the future.

355
00:25:07.791 --> 00:25:11.250
Our Special Sciences Division
is flying in to dismantle Master Mold.

356
00:25:11.750 --> 00:25:14.708
Yet again.
humanity is in the X-Men's debt.

357
00:25:15.666 --> 00:25:19.165
Trask would rather humans and mutants
go to war than work together.

358
00:25:19.166 --> 00:25:21.707
We all win when men like him fail.

359
00:25:21.708 --> 00:25:23.624
You sound like Charles.

360
00:25:23.625 --> 00:25:25.208
He would have been proud today.

361
00:25:27.666 --> 00:25:31.708
Thank you. Dr. Cooper.
But to be honest. it was a team effort.

362
00:25:33.458 --> 00:25:34.833
Always has been.

363
00:25:37.291 --> 00:25:38.624
Team's on their way back.

364
00:25:38.625 --> 00:25:39.790
Mission accomplished.

365
00:25:39.791 --> 00:25:43.208
Freedom! I mean.
I'll get out of your hair.

366
00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:47.040
Look. I know today was strange.

367
00:25:47.041 --> 00:25:50.625
When I first came here.
I ran away. just like you.

368
00:25:51.166 --> 00:25:53.957
The team had saved me
from Sentinels at the mall.

369
00:25:53.958 --> 00:25:55.040
But this place.

370
00:25:55.041 --> 00:25:59.957
a place where I could be me.
where a foster brat belonged.

371
00:25:59.958 --> 00:26:03.124
that was scarier than any killer robot.

372
00:26:03.125 --> 00:26:06.374
Sure. Cyclops still won't
let me fly the jet.

373
00:26:06.375 --> 00:26:08.500
but this isn't some weird school.

374
00:26:09.375 --> 00:26:10.458
It's a family.

375
00:26:11.500 --> 00:26:12.875
A family that accepts you.

376
00:26:13.958 --> 00:26:15.041
Sounds nice.

377
00:26:16.458 --> 00:26:18.833
Your parents don't know. do they?

378
00:26:21.958 --> 00:26:24.082
Some sort of solar energy.

379
00:26:24.083 --> 00:26:25.499
Still figuring it out.

380
00:26:25.500 --> 00:26:28.082
Makes me strong. though. Really strong.

381
00:26:28.083 --> 00:26:31.290
Whenever I do this.
it just reminds me that I'm different.

382
00:26:31.291 --> 00:26:33.000
That I'm lying to them.

383
00:26:33.833 --> 00:26:35.291
Be an X-Man. Jubilee?

384
00:26:36.208 --> 00:26:37.625
I don't even want to be myself.

385
00:26:42.375 --> 00:26:43.957
Here.

386
00:26:43.958 --> 00:26:45.790
What's your job? Hot and rich?

387
00:26:45.791 --> 00:26:47.415
Don't forget single.

388
00:26:47.416 --> 00:26:49.790
Page me. I got a jet. too.

389
00:26:49.791 --> 00:26:51.791
Maybe I'll even let you fly it.

390
00:26:57.083 --> 00:26:58.957
Remember. no powers.

391
00:26:58.958 --> 00:27:01.333
What about Gambit's other powers?

392
00:27:03.041 --> 00:27:07.041
The responsibility to choose teams
falls to team leader.

393
00:27:08.958 --> 00:27:11.832
I know I've been hardheaded lately.
It's just...

394
00:27:11.833 --> 00:27:14.541
I didn't know how the X-Men
could go on without the Professor.

395
00:27:15.208 --> 00:27:16.541
Thought it was on me.

396
00:27:17.208 --> 00:27:20.000
But his dream doesn't need me.

397
00:27:20.625 --> 00:27:21.750
It has all of you.

398
00:27:22.416 --> 00:27:26.249
And with that said.
Jean and I have an announcement.

399
00:27:26.250 --> 00:27:30.415
You're bailing on us to go raise
your little one someplace nice and normal.

400
00:27:30.416 --> 00:27:32.500
Logan. we're not bailing.

401
00:27:32.833 --> 00:27:35.915
Cyclops and Jean were the first X-Men.

402
00:27:35.916 --> 00:27:38.999
If they're gone.
who the heck is going to lead the team?

403
00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:40.874
<i>Intruder alert!</i>

404
00:27:40.875 --> 00:27:44.291
Sensors show the intruder
has breached the Professor's old office.

405
00:27:46.833 --> 00:27:50.582
Charles Xavier
was the finest man I knew.

406
00:27:50.583 --> 00:27:52.624
Despite our differences.

407
00:27:52.625 --> 00:27:55.040
he never ceased
to have faith in our friendship.

408
00:27:55.041 --> 00:27:57.457
nor forgive my many failings.

409
00:27:57.458 --> 00:28:01.207
Perhaps that is why
the old fool has done this.

410
00:28:01.208 --> 00:28:04.249
Magneto.
what are you doing in our home?

411
00:28:04.250 --> 00:28:07.957
Your home? I beg to differ. Cyclops.

412
00:28:07.958 --> 00:28:12.915
The last will and testament
of Charles Francis Xavier.

413
00:28:12.916 --> 00:28:14.957
As you all will see.

414
00:28:14.958 --> 00:28:17.874
his fortune. his school.

415
00:28:17.875 --> 00:28:22.250
everything he built.
everything he fought for.

416
00:28:22.791 --> 00:28:27.125
now belongs to me. my X-Men.
